 A women told the police that she was hijacked. On investigation police found that the lady’s boyfriend actually took the car following a lover’s quarrel.
He didn’t have money to pay for a taxi to take him to Ermelo, and decided to take his girlfriend’s car keys and left. Police traced the car to the boyfriend’s house in Ermelo. Police didn’t name the women or her boyfriend but the woman will be charged with perjury.    Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za